l AMR parsers miss. This differs from Paper 1 by moving beyond NED to full semantic graph generation, from Paper 2 by being supervised and integrated within parsing rather than unsupervised extraction, and from Paper 3 by operating at the cross-sentence, discourse-level semantics via AMR rather than sentence-local triples. The novelty lies in unifying knowledge-enhanced representation learning with deep semantic parsing in biomedicine—a previously unexplored synergy.

